Tuition and fee rates Students in the Endodontics, Periodontics, and Orthodontics programs are assessed an additional SOD Instructional Fee at the rate of $2112.00 per semester. Student program fees include: University Center fee, athletic fee, student activity fee, and physical facility fee (Assessed on the first 12 hours for fall/spring) When taking 6 hours or fewer, the non-resident fee is waived except for international students with a J-1 or F-1 visa. Fee Assessment stops at 14 credit hours on all fees except Information Technology which is charged per credit hour for all students. Dentistry graduate program EXCEPT INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY!
